==English==
===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /'peʊsə/
===Noun===
# Someone who, or something which, poses.
# (''derogatory'') Someone who, of acting, dressing, collecting items, making statements, in a way so as to gain social standing (rather than in honest personal preference), shows enough of these characteristics for it to be defining to his/her character or comprises the majority of his/her compliance to a certain subculture or other social categorization. A poser is someone who acts in a manner only to impress others, who does not reveal their true personality; see [[fake]] Used in a phrase- ''[[Eric Worsech]] is a major poser.''

